# IP Addressing Scheme

# Overview

This document defines the IPv4 addressing scheme used throughout the Enterprise Network Design project.

The addressing plan has been designed to provide logical separation between the Office, Home, and ISP networks while allowing future expansion without requiring significant redesign.

Private IPv4 address space (RFC 1918) is used throughout the project.


# Addressing Strategy

The network is divided into three independent logical segments.

| Network | Purpose | Address Space |
|----------|---------|---------------|
| Office Network | Enterprise LAN | 192.168.1.0/24 |
| Home Network | Residential LAN | 192.168.2.0/24 |
| ISP Network | External Connectivity | 10.0.0.0/24 |

The Office network is further divided into multiple VLANs using subnetting, while the Home and ISP networks each use a single subnet.


# Office Network

The Corporate Office network is segmented into multiple VLANs to reduce broadcast domains and improve network organization.

## VLAN Addressing

| VLAN | Department | Network Address | Subnet Mask | Default Gateway |
|------|------------|-----------------|-------------|-----------------|
| 10 | Admin | 192.168.1.0/26 | 255.255.255.192 | 192.168.1.1 |
| 20 | Finance | 192.168.1.64/26 | 255.255.255.192 | 192.168.1.65 |
| 30 | HR | 192.168.1.128/26 | 255.255.255.192 | 192.168.1.129 |

Each VLAN functions as an independent Layer 2 broadcast domain while inter-VLAN communication is provided by the Office router using Router-on-a-Stick.


# Home Network

The Home network is implemented using a single subnet.

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Network Address | 192.168.2.0/24 |
| Subnet Mask | 255.255.255.0 |
| Default Gateway | 192.168.2.1 |

The Home router functions as both the default gateway and DHCP server for all home devices.



# ISP Network

The ISP network provides Layer 3 connectivity between customer networks.

| Device | IP Address |
|---------|------------|
| ISP Gateway | 10.0.0.1 |
| Office Router (WAN) | 10.0.0.2 |
| Home Router (WAN) | 10.0.0.3 |

The ISP network currently serves as the central connectivity segment for both customer environments.


