# Addressing Design Considerations

The addressing scheme has been designed with the following objectives:

- Separate Office, Home, and ISP environments.
- Provide dedicated address space for each Office VLAN.
- Support automatic IP assignment through DHCP.
- Reserve infrastructure addresses for routers and network devices.
- Allow future expansion without major changes to the existing addressing plan.

The modular addressing structure simplifies routing, troubleshooting, and future implementation of enterprise services such as NAT, DNS, ACLs, and dynamic routing protocols.


# Summary

The project currently uses five logical IP networks.

| Network | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| 192.168.1.0/26 | Office VLAN 10 |
| 192.168.1.64/26 | Office VLAN 20 |
| 192.168.1.128/26 | Office VLAN 30 |
| 192.168.2.0/24 | Home Network |
| 10.0.0.0/24 | ISP Network |

This addressing plan provides a scalable foundation for future enhancements while maintaining logical separation between network segments.